==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pneumatology
<hw>Pneu`ma*tol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pneumato-</ets> + <ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pneumatologie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The doctrine of, or a
treatise on, air and other elastic fluids. See <er>Pneumatics</er>,
1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Philos. & Theol.)</fld> <def>The science of
spiritual being or phenomena of any description.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pneumatometer</ent>⟦br⟧
